In another scene , Ronan The Accuser is mad at korath for failing & tells him that he promised to Thanos to retrieve the orb to power his infinity gauntlet to destroy xandar. It's way too super-hero movie generic. 600 billion lives lie in the balance, or whatever, but we know that at least planet Earth is safe because without it, there'd be no Avengers 2. Wish they'd have stuck with making trailers that were more offbeat in spirit.

text: @Vince Sansano Right in front of all of you. Most people are just not making an effort to find them. Use the internet. Find the independent stuff, the stuff from foreign filmmakers etc. It's there, it just takes a bit of effort to see it. Remember Martin Scorsese's Hugo? That wasn't a film about fighting and war (despite World War 1) being mentioned a few times. And what about Wes Anderson's The Grand Budapest Hotel? It does have some fighting in it, and gunfights, but ultimately that is not what it is about. There is also the French, Oscar-arwarded animated film The Illusionist. People just like these fighting things more, I guess, and honestly, it's NOT something new. Fighting, wars, killing and heroism has been part of the most popular fiction since Anciet Greece, with all the plays and poems. And I don't think it's really ever going to change...

Even the Avengers kind of followed this mold (though, they did it very well). It's not a bad way to make movies but it's getting old. X-men is probably the biggest exception to this, but this movie does not seem to be at least from this trailer.
